args:
Mordecai tries to support Ilia, who worries
whether or not she made the right decision.
But when the group escapes a burning forest,
they are attacked by enraged dragons and
saved in the nick of time by the Windwyrm.
We just need to get out of this forest!
(I can't believe he'd burn down the woods\nto keep us from hiding here.)
(If the woods burn, the mana will be\ndisrupted and the dragons will rage.)
(Did I do the right thing? Should I have\ngiven him the key? I just don't know...)
Meene, Zethia, go on ahead.\nI will carry Ilia and follow.
You'd better take care of her.
Come, Ilia. Get on my back.
I can't believe I summoned you into\nsuch a crappy world.
You were innocent and beautiful,\nand now I've defiled you.
What? What are you talking about...?

How else can you look at it?
The moment I brought you here and gave
you a body, it's been one lousy escapade
after another.
I didn't call you here to live in the suck.
I wanted to teach you about the world and\nshow you emotions and let you see all\nthe wonderful things you've never known!
But now I'm just making things worse.
I don't know what's right, I don't know what\nchoice will lead me to the future I want...\nI don't know a damn thing.
And all that not-knowing scares me.
But what REALLY scares me is the thought\nthat I might not be able to protect you.
So that's why I think you should go.
Take off! Be free! Find somewhere nice\nwhere you're not burdened by me and\nall of my terrible decisions!
Do you not understand what I'm saying?\nI want you to be free!
There is no meaning or purpose to\nanything if I can't be with you.
That is what love means to me, and it is\nwhy I will be with you until the very end.\nHave I understood that correctly?
I guess I DID tell you that love was\nsort of an individual thing, huh?
So if that's your answer, I can't tell you\nit's wrong—I just hope you don't regret it.
I am confident I will not.\nNow let us leave this forest.
They haven't come out of the forest yet...
They are all right. I'm certain of it.\n...Please be all right.
That's it. I'm going in there.
No! You mustn't! It's too dangerous!
My life is nothing compared to Ilia!
Hey, guys! Sorry to keep you waiting.
I'm so relieved to see you both.
You need to be healed. Come here.
I am glad everyone is well, but we failed\nto act regarding the bombs in the city.
And the woods were burned, which will\nonly stoke the dragons' fury.
So instead of helping, we made it WORSE.\nI almost don't want to ask what everyone\nthinks we should do next...
I think they're headed for the capital.\nWe have to stop them!
KILL THE HUMANS! KILL THEM ALL!
Please, stop! We don't want to fight you!
THEN WHY DID YOU BURN THE WILDS\nAND THE WOODS? WHY DID YOU KILL\nOUR BRETHREN AND KIN?
WE WILL KILL THE HUMANS WHO KILLED\nOUR DRAGON BRETHREN! KILL! KILL! KILL!
They are blinded with rage.\nWe've no choice but to run.
Run WHERE? The woods are on fire\nand there are dragons everywhere.\nI think this really is the end...
(That's the same name as the Windwyrm\nfrom the Mistholt, and this mana is his\nas well... Yet he is clearly different!)
Calm yourselves, my fellows!\nKilling humans will not return our kin!
Not even Midgardsormr could take down\nthis many dragons. We need to help him.
We won't make a dent against an entire\npack of dragons!
Then the four of us will work together\nand defeat them one by one.
If even one gets by, the city will explode.\nWe have no choice but to act.
I agree, though it terrifies me.
Let us quell their fury together!
